      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 128,
      "message": "NO! This message is parsed to retrieve the ModuleSetTag for the upgrade. Setting to 'not-specified' led to failures, which this fixes.\n\nI am planning a different fix that does not rely on this message at all - my plan is to set the CM-handle's moduleSetTag to the upgraded one at the same time that the handle goes to LOCKED state for MODULE_UPGRADE. Then we are free to put whatever we want in this message.",
